# DP Observation

To reach stair i:

cost[i] + minimum(
    i-1,
    i-2
)

Therefore:

dp[i] = cost[i] + min(dp[i-1], dp[i-2])

Answer:

min(dp[n-1], dp[n-2])

---

# Approach 1: Recursion

At every stair:

min(
    solve(i-1),
    solve(i-2)
)

Time Complexity:
O(2^N)

Space Complexity:
O(N)

---

# Approach 2: Memoization

Store previously calculated answers.

Time Complexity:
O(N)

Space Complexity:
O(N)

---

# Approach 3: Tabulation

Build dp array from left to right.

Time Complexity:
O(N)

Space Complexity:
O(N)

---

# Approach 4: Space Optimization

Only previous two values are needed.

Time Complexity:
O(N)

Space Complexity:
O(1)

---

# Recurrence Relation

f(i) = cost[i] + min(
            f(i-1),
            f(i-2)
        )

Base Cases:

f(0) = cost[0]

f(1) = cost[1]

